# React Patterns

## Components

- Default export function components with PascalCase filenames.
- Props as `interface XProps { ... }` by default.
- Keep components under 250 lines when possible.
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
interface StageCardProps {
  title: string;
  isActive: boolean;
}

export default function StageCard({ title, isActive }: StageCardProps) {
  return <div>{title}</div>;
}
```

## Client Boundary

Add `"use client"` only when the component uses:

- React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, etc.)
- Browser APIs (`document`, `window`, scroll listeners)
- Client-only libraries (Chart.js, interactive Font Awesome)

Sections one and two are Server Components. Sections three and four are Client Components.

## Logic Extraction

- Reusable React hooks → `hooks/` (named exports, e.g. `useDecodeText`)
- Pure non-React logic → `lib/` (e.g. `decode-text.ts`)
- Page/route UI → `app/_components/` (e.g. `sections/`, `stage/`)
- Shared reusable UI → `components/` (e.g. `chart/RadarChart`)

## State

- Local `useState` only. No global state libraries.
